First let me start by saying a big thank-you for sharing your expertise with me, and I’m sure I am speaking for the collective too!  I am a grandmother of 6 month old baby girls, and I take care of them about 4 days a week.  Let me tell ya…I spend a lot of time on the floor “moving” around with them in all kinds of positions.  I am in fairly good shape, but this journey has made me so much more aware of my movements and how to use my breath to safely navigate my way around their little wiggly bodies (their happy baby and super man poses are perfect too!) I think of you everyday because of it, and I send you prayers of thanksgiving!  You also make me bust out laughing often…like today, “wait what I didn’t sign up for this!”  Much love to you Adrienne…🐾 The tea is so good too:)

Dear Adriene,  Today’s practice I felt so comforted and full of love, which is something I realised we can make as part of our everyday life! We will have many more moons to go, and asking ourselves, “How am I feeling?” matched with “How do I want to feel?” empowers us in so many ways. I am currently listening to Louise Hay’s book, _“The Power is Within You”_ and when we treat ourselves with tendering loving kindness, we create a much better relationship with ourselves that is filled with joy and love all our live long days. Thank you Adriene, for your wonderful TLC to all of us. With love, Emily

This practice (especially after yesterday's practice) makes me think of a philosophy that bell hooks proposed. Grossly paraphrased here, it has to do with the stories that we are often most familiar with: the hero's journey. There's always a battle, a fight, and a conquering. And I love Star Wars, but we are all too familiar with aggression and violence because of a history of colonialism, societys' hierarchies, oppression, or stories in pop culture. Instead, what if we took a journey of love? Just love. The mantra of "I am strong" can be interpreted in so many ways! I am reminded to take care of myself and others, and maybe, just maybe, through my strength of love, I can achieve what I want, which will, in turn, will make the world a better place.
Happy Saturday! Bring this TLC mindset to any place you go, today and always!

How are you feeling and how do you want to feel? I loved being asked those questions and have a breathing moment to check in. I am very exhausted and low on energy this week. How I want to feel: Confident, capable and stabile. I really find the mat is the way to achieving it. The connection to how I feel and the movement closer to how I want to feel. 
Yoga is so diverse, from an intensity like a workout to a soft snuggle almost like a meditation. Yoga is presenting you within the movements and philosophy so much about how life is in general. And how I conquer one movement every day on the mat teaches me so much about myself off the mat. Yoga is a way of living, it truly is.
